    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: HORTON ON/OFF - DISASSEMBLE - BEARING REPLACEMENT (SPLINED HUB)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="3">
        <title>BEARING REPLACEMENT (SPLINED HUB)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove adjusting nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200414">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200414" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200414" filename="../figg12/G1200414.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Removing Adjusting Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide splined hub off journal (Item 1,
                <hotlnk document="s12004r_15.xml" xrefid="f1200415">Figure 22</hotlnk>) to remove bearings (Items 1 and
                3,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200416">Figure 15</hotlnk>) from splined hub piston.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200416" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200415" filename="../figg12/G1200415.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Splined Hub With Bearings, Exploded View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HUB BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BEARING SPACER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HUB BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HUB SPLINED PISTON</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Relocate spacer (Item 2,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200416">Figure 15</hotlnk>) to one side; then, using a drift placed on the inner
                bearing race, tap out bearing while working drift around inner bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200417">Figure 16</hotlnk>). Repeat procedure remaining bearing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200417" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200416" filename="../figg12/G1200416.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Tapping Out Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Bearings are removed in opposite directions. Do not reuse bearings that have been removed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">While fully supporting splined hub, press new bearing (Item 3,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200416">Figure 15</hotlnk>) into place.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install spacer (Item 2,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200416">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>All bearings are prelubricated and sealed; do not remove seals to lubricate bearings or fill
                        bearing void with grease.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">While still fully supporting splined hub, press the bearing (Item 1,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200416">Figure 15</hotlnk>) into place.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
